| Galapagos Islands Environment "In Danger"                          |
|   from the bye-finches-bye-iguanas dept.                           |
|   posted by kdawson on Saturday June 30, @21:19 (Education)        |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/01/016205       |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

cagrin writes "On Tuesday the UN's World Heritage Committee [0]added the
Galapagos Islands to the list of sites in danger from environmental
threats or overuse. From the article: 'The Galapagos Islands, an
Ecuadorian territory situated in the Pacific Ocean some 1,000 kilometers
(625 miles) from South America, helped shape Charles Darwin's theory of
evolution and in 1978 was the first site placed on UNESCO's World
Heritage List.' Here is some background from Sea Shepherd on the
[1]insults facing the Galapagos."

