| Science Videos Search Engine                                       |
|   from the do-mentos-and-coke-count-as-science-yet dept.           |
|   posted by CmdrTaco on Sunday July 01, @09:31 (Media)             |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/01/1241250      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Rami writes "[1]ScienceHack is a search engine for science videos.
What makes ScienceHack unique is that every video is screened by a
scientist or an engineer to verify the video's accuracy and quality.
ScienceHack focuses on many topics including physics, chemistry and
biology. If you go to YouTube to search for videos, you will get spam
videos and comments and many conspiracy and low quality videos.
ScienceHack has none of that. ScienceHack currently supports videos from
YouTube, Google videos and Metacafe."
[1]http://sciencehack.com/

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/07/01/1241250

