| FastTCP Commercialized Into An FTP Appliance                       |
|   from the speedy-delivery dept.                                   |
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday July 01, @13:33 (Communications)        |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/01/1718221     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]prostoalex writes "[1]FastTCP technology, developed by researchers at
CalTech, is being commercialized. A company called FastSoft has
introduced [2]a hardware appliance that delivers 15x-20x faster FTP
transmissions than those delivered via regular TCP. Says eWeek: 'The
algorithm implemented in the Aria appliance senses congestion by
continuously measuring the round-trip time for the TCP acknowledgment and
then monitoring how that measurement changes from moment to moment.'"

Discuss this story at:
    http://hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/07/01/1718221

